gov.usgs.anss.inventory

Class MaintLog

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.inventory.MaintLog

  • public class MaintLog
extends java.lang.Object
    MaintLog.java - This class represent a transaction on a trackable item. Each operation creates one of these. A "maint needed" is entered with a completed date in 1970. If the name of the class does not match the name of the field in the class you may need to modify the rs.getSTring in the constructor. Created on July 8, 2002, 1:23 PM

      • MaintLog

        public MaintLog(int inID,
                int item,
                java.lang.String type,
                int code,
                java.lang.String desc,
                java.lang.String ops,
                java.lang.String rma_in,
                java.sql.Date comp)
        Build from raw arguments. The database is not updated with this info but it behaves as a normal MaintLog
        Parameters:
        inID - The DB ID
        item - The DB ID of the item this maintlog is concerning
        type - The type from the Enum in the database definition
        code - A maintenance code from the tables of the same name
        desc - Text describing this transaction on the item
        ops - Must match the Enum in database file for the status at this trans
        rma_in - A RMA string
        comp - The date this maint item was completed.
